cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the calibration of heterogeneous sensors (radar and camera) for intelligent transportation systems. The use of convolutional neural networks and boosting-inspired training algorithm suggests that it falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The application of the method to the field of robotics and automation (cs.RO) is also evident. Additionally, the use of real-world data and the focus on system operation and generalization suggest that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY) categories.
